|CKBLoad Weapon: Improvements Made While You Wait Nervously|000

Syntax: loadweapon <weapon> with <dazzling|oiled|silvered|flaming|frozen|poisoned|shocking>

Treat a carried, unwielded, ordinary weapon. Unique pieces refuse the work,
presumably on advice from better lawyers.

  Dazzling
    Contraband 1, Alchemy 50. A shifting finish leaves the weapon Razzled.
    "Flash" remains accepted when ordering.

  Oiled
    Contraband 2, Alchemy 70. Makes the weapon markedly easier to place. The
    benefit takes hold as soon as the weapon is ready again.

  Poisoned
    Contraband 2, Alchemy 100. Adds a direct poison treatment. Stretch Poison
    remains the better way to preserve a prepared poison's special payload.

  Flaming / Frozen
    Contraband 3, Alchemy 100. Adds fire or cold to each convincing strike,
    which may leave the victim Burning or Chilled.

  Silvered
    Contraband 4, Alchemy 125, Smithing 50, and one saved Silver Bar. Leaves
    the weapon Silvered. "Quicksilver" remains accepted when ordering.

  Shocking
    Contraband 4, Alchemy 150. Adds lightning and a slim chance that the
    victim's muscles briefly reconsider their obligations.

Greater trade skill improves the treatment's strength and lifetime. Every
load has a drawback. Dazzling can very rarely steal concentration; Sharpened
weapons made elsewhere can very rarely leave a foe Bleeding. If it did not
have fine print, someone reputable would sell it.
